	A+++++ YOU WON'T BE DISAPPOINTED	We stayed at the Carlton Hotel from 22 November for 3 nights and to be honest I tried to change our booking following reading the negative reviews on tripadvisor. I couldn't get the booking changed so held my breath and hoped for the best. How glad I am that we had to go to the Carlton. The hotel is situated on Sutter Street which is about a 15 minute walk from Union Square, I know everyone keeps going on about the front desk staff but they have to be seen to be believed they are so helpful and friendly, really genuine and really do go the extra mile to make sure you have a great stay. Our room was based at the back of the hotel and had a massive bed, the room and bathroom were both tastefully decorated. The hotel is near the Tenderloin area which is not the best area in the city, but the staff do warn you on checkin not to go near it, we unfortunately wondered into it and did feel very threatened and vulnerable, although no one approached or even spoke to us, but we had been warned and should have paid more attention to where we were going.Other reviews have also stated that the walls are paper thin in the hotel, I can categorically state that I am a light sleeper and I did not hear a single sound from the other rooms during our entire stay. I certainly could hear traffic and fire sirens but hey what do you expect if you are staying in the middle of a major city.I really don't know what the negative reviewers are talking about, I am so glad I took a chance and stayed at this wonderful hotel.	
	Brilliant hotel with loads of character and staff to match	We stayed here for 3 nights from the 22-25 November 2009. On arriving at the hotel, we were greated by Theo at the reception, he has loads of character, very professional cheery and funny. Check- In was easy and he instantly asked if we needed direction to anywhere or tours organised. He gave us a map, and pointed out how to get to Fisherman's wharf which was a number 47 bus from Van Ness Av, this was a short 5 min walk to the stop. He also explained we were within walking distance of the main shopping area. Do not miss Macy's or Westfield Shopping Centre.Only slight grumble was the rooms was a bit noisy as we could hear the guy next dooe coughing quite loudly so not Theo also explained that the hotel had a 5.30 Wine reception every night, to meet fellow travellers. We made this every night, Theo provided the music by playing the keyboard in the hotel. We met load of people from our neck of the woods, who had been on our cruise previous to this who were staying at the hotel, we had brilliant time at the reception as everybody made a point of being back for this.The breakfast in the hotel is expensive, but loads of cafe's etc around the hotel, hotel recommended Wing Lum the chinese for dinner, this is not much to look at inside, but food was excellent (1 portion between 2 is loads) and we passed on our knowledge to 2 other groups who also ate there. Also Little Henry is a lovely Italian cafe/diner with typical good italian food, run by a chinese family all reasonably priced. Alcatraz is not to be missed	
