Nov 6 2009 	Friendly Funky and Fun	We stayed at the Hotel Carlton while my spouse attended a convention in nearby Union Square. I found this hotel to be a true delight. The rooms were clean, modern and stylish. I was impressed with their environmental emphasis which included filtered water available on each floor to avoid having to buy bottled water. Also, great free Internet service in every room. The front desk staff were charming, helpful, had great senses of humor, and went out of their way to create a friendly and hospitable atmosphere. As for the neighborhood, this is not exactly Nob Hill, but on the other hand, it is not dangerous and the hotel is adjacent to some of the best Thai and Vietnamese food I've eaten. Once again, a recommendation from Theo of the front desk set us in the right direction for a truly terrific meal. If you want staid and stodgy, perhaps this hotel won't be your thing, but if you are after a clean, modern, and fun place with lots of hospitality and charm, you can't go wrong with the Hotel Carlton.	
