Oct 21 2009 	Solid 3 star hotel with a great staff and expensive parking	I was in San Francisco for a large conference @ Moscone Center, and it was fleet week to boot. The hotel scene was tight and this is what I ended up with. It's in a nice neighborhood - but you're going to have to hike/taxi/drive to the attractions and BART is nowhere close by. It's an older hotel, a nice lounge in the first floor, great desk staff and generally pretty clean. I had a good stay at this hotel, but here are a couple things you should know: It's central heat, you have no control of the heat in your room, full power when the system is on, cold when it's off. If you are staying in the warm season I did not see any aircon. Parking, valet only at the hotel, is $30/night +tax and when I arrived all the local lots were full - there really are only a handful of small parking lots around the hotel so you are likely to be stuck with valet if your are driving. Other than that it was a nice hotel. A wine tasting in the evening, a Zagat rated restaurant onsite - although I did not try it. Would I stay here again - maybe - but I'd sure work Priceline pretty hard first, there are better deals to be had.	
