Oct 4 2009 	Well placed comfortable friendly 3-star hotel	We stayed here for the final 4-nights of our 3-week tour of the west-USA following recommendations on Tripadvisor. We booked the stay through Expdedia and got a great rate as a part of a sale event.The hotel is situated near the downtown area of San Fran and ideally placed to catch the public transport system. The Carlton is a very good 3-star hotel with very friendly and helpful staff. There have been some comments on previous Tripadvisor entries regarding the hotel and the street noise at lower floor levels. We stayed on floor 6 and heard first-hand from a guest who was on the 1st floor, finding the street noise unbearable. So, thanks to those who pointed out that the higher floors are better! Also make sure you have a room that isn't next to the lift shafts!The on site restaurant, SAHA offers arabic-fusion food - highly recommended! A great atmosphere in the restaurant and the food was brilliant.There are bars and restaurants around the hotel; a supermarket right around the corner &quot;Walgreens&quot; (on the corner of Larkin and Bush), and Union Square is a 15-minute walk down Sutter Street. To get around you must use the public transport system - &quot;Sutter Fine Foods&quot; sells 3-day passes for $18 per person and it's well worth it.Free internet access another bonus to the hotel, and there are two PC's near reception with a printer (first 20 minutes on internet is free).No fridge in the room which would have been nice, although there is a safe.There is no air-con, but the windows can be opened fully. The ceiling fan offered good air circulation and the temperature in the city during our stay was pretty comfortable, but I can imagine the room being quite uncomfortable in the height of summer!Free wine evenings from 530pm for an hour in the lobby - a nice touch offered by the hotel - and a good way to mingle.In summary - a real gem in the city, a good quality 3-star hotel and we'd definitely recommend and would go back if visitting San Fran again!	
