Aug 9 2009 	Good stay at the Hotel Carlton	Recently returned from a road trip of California, travelling down the Pacific Coast Highway. Our first stop was 4 nights in the Hotel Carlton and it was a good start to our vacation. The hotel is located in a good position, about 6 blocks from Union Square. There are a couple of bars close by but we didn't eat nearby so can't recommend any local restaurants. We ate breakfast in the hotel restaurant and it was nice but didn't have any evening meals there. They served a good selection of breakfast options, including some unusual choices but very tasty.The room was okay, a nice size for a city hotel with a walk in closet. We were on the front of the hotel and it could get a little noisy but it didn't bother us. If you are a very light sleeper then you might want to request a room at the back. Also, my brother said that the walls were paper thin and you could hear the next rooms conversation. We didn't experience the same problem but again it could get annoying if you're a light sleeper.We really enjoyed the wine reception in the evening from 5.30 to 6.00. We couldn't believe how many people were there each evening and I'm sure there were some free loaders who just turned up for the wine and then left. The hotel didn't ask to see a room key so anyone could walk in and have some free wine and leave with no questions asked. The staff were extremely friendly and ordered cabs for us and booked us some restaurant reservations. We had some lovely meals and one horrible experience at the House of Nanking (chinatown). I have posted a separate review of the restaurant but avoid like the plague!! Worst service ever experienced in 40 years.The weather was very disappointing but apparantely that's typical for July / August when the fog tends to be at it's worst. We've been in October previously and the weather was gorgeous. We only took a couple of long sleeved jumpers so they got a lot of wear over the 4 days!!Would recommend the Duck Tour, especially if you've got young children. It was great fun.We would certainly stay in the Carlton again and recommend to others.	
