Jul 27 2009 	I would stay there again but not during the winter months	I stayed at this hotel during a spell of cool, chilly, rainy weather -- cloudy with highs about 50 and overnight lows about 40 -- weather that is not atypical for San Francisco in the months of December through March. This is an older property, and the principal heat source consists old-fashioned radiators. The heat never came on regularly enough for long enough in my room to feel really comfortable. The hotel was able to supply a space heater for supplemental heat, but the staff indicated that the unit I received was the last one available. Generally I like the hotel and the location, and the Saha restaurant on-site is first-rate. But I would probably only choose to stay there again during the warmer weather months. I did mention this issue to the hotel management in a post-stay survey, and I expressed the view that I hoped they would eventually install a more modern heating system, acknowledging the difficulty of doing so in an older building. I was offered a discount on a subsequent stay because my stay was sub-optimal. The offer doesn't alter my opinion, though, about when I would be willing to stay again. I should also mention that I received a significant discount from the rack rate for my stay, which influences my view of the value for the money. I have no way of knowing whether the the fact that I was a discount customer affected my room assignment (possibly to a less well-heated part of the building?).	
