Jul 18 2009 	Quaint Hotel Superb Customer Service	The Carlton Hotel is truly one of the most enjoyable experiences I have had in a long time. Every summer I make a major trip, providing me the opportunity to have many hotel experiences. By far, the customer service, the cleanliness &amp; comfort, the eclectic styling, and the great location make the Carlton the best lodging choice in San Francisco.ProsExcellent customer service at the hotel desk--willing to help you with any question you might have (great travel agents!), comfortable beds, bathrooms with a luxurious feel, availability of basic toiletries (shower has 3 dispensers for shampoo, conditioner and soap--no more tiny bottles), good-sized rooms for a boutique hotel, and a fabulous location--three major bus lines run practically next to the hotel, getting you most anywhere you would want to go; also, it's location was great, walking distant for many of the major sights. Have I mentioned the customer service? Every time we left or came back, we were personally greeted. They even asked us how we were finding the town and if they could help. I have never seen such attentive hotel staff. Our maid even left us a Happy 4th of July note in our room one day. How sweet is that! Additionally, the decor has this Asian eclectic Zen feel, making it so inviting, warm, and friendly; I felt like I was visiting a friend's home. It was such a welcoming place at the end of a long sight-seeing day.Things to be aware of: --no breakfast served (single serve coffee pots in room)--not too many restaurant choices right near the hotel (but if you are willing to walk, you will find something)--the walls are not industrially sound-proofed. You will hear some noise from your neighbors and can tell when doors are being opened/shut. So, if you are a princess and the pea kind of sleeper, I just wanted to give you the heads up.However, I cannot brag enough on this fabulous hotel establishment. It is comfortable, clean, and customer friendly. I would highly recommend it to any traveler going to San Francisco.--It is a pretty easy 30-minute walk to the wharf from the hotel, but WARNING it is an almost completely UPHILL walk on the way back--that is why I suggest bus #19 that runs on Polk, just a couple blocks from the hotel.--Same thing with Chinatown; relatively easy walk to it, but the walk back has many hills--again, take the bus.	
