Jul 4 2009 	Friendly clean comfortable hotel	Spent two nights here in June 2009.We were met by a very friendly and helpful front desk, just what you need after an 11 hour flight. They pointed out places to eat, public transport and the one area of the city to avoid (the Tenderloin district).The room was spacious, very clean although we were woken by a trash cart at around 4 in the morning, collecting the trash and glass bottles.The hotel is in a pretty good location for downtown, about 15 - 20 minutes walk from Union Square. It is also only 10 minutes from Dotties True Blue Cafe, for the best ever breakfasts (make sure you get there about 10 minutes before it opens at 7.30, otherwise you'll have a lengthy wait for a table).We didn't eat in the restaurant as we felt it was a bit pricy, so cant comment on the food, but there are plenty of good ones in walking distance. One drawback, the hotel didn't have a bar, but again, there are plenty nearby.	
