Jun 30 2009 	Great hotel despite the location	Our 2 nights' stay at Hotel Carlton in early June was excellent!  After getting off at Powell Street, we walked for close to 20 minutes before we reached the hotel. Even though it's located in the &quot;Lower Nob Hill&quot; region, and a couple blocks away from the shady &quot;Tenderloin&quot; area, we felt safe there. The warm greetings from the front desk when we first stepped into the hotel was nice. And the entire check-in process took only 3 minutes. The deluxe room on the 7th floor has great lighting, and the room is well laid out. Even though there's no air-conditioner in the room, the breeze from the opened window and the ceiling fan was more than enough. This hotel prides itself on being environmentally friendly. So instead of bottled water, they place a glass pitcher in the room and you to get filtered water from either 1st or 8th floor. What a good ideal! We booked our room directly on the joie de vivre website, and got a fantastic deal: $99 room/day including daily breakfast for two at their Zaha Restaurant. Let me just tell you, their french toast is out of this world!!!!!!! Lightly battered toasts with a caramelized, crispy outside and soft (not mushy) inside, topped with fresh blueberries and strawberries. Just writing about it me makes drool..... This was our first time staying at a JDV hotel, and what an experience that was! I highly recommend this hotel to anyone who's looking for a clean room, friendly service, great food and most of all, unbeatable deal! Thank you, Hotel Carlton, for a wonderful time.	
Jun 30 2009 	Friendly clean and comfortable.	An environmentally conscious hotel. The staff are efficient, helpful, and friendly. The room was clean and comfortable. Great value for location and service.	
Jun 26 2009 	exceptional front desk	pros: Front desk staff, especially bellhop, very attentive to guests. Went out of way to make sure I felt better when suffering from jetlag.Good location, able to catch trolley or MUNI bus easily within short walking distance.Very clean and stylishly decorated. Bed is comfortable enough.Cozy lobby, and delicious restaurant on site.cons: this is a &quot;green&quot; hotel. Be forewarned! The towels are scratchy. The toilet paper is thin and scratchy. You don't get the cool little bottles of shampoo and conditioner that most hotels provide in your room. There are NO extras.Also, a note about the shower curtain. There is no plastic liner, which means neither curtain repels water. You will end up with a flood on the bathroom floor when you get out if you don't put BOTH shower curtains inside the tub when you shower!The restaurant on site is not open very many hours of the day. In fact, it is closed Sun and Mon nites.And one final note, there is no continental breakfast. As a Southern girl, I'm used to those, and I was a little disappointed.	
