May 16 2009 	Excellent hotel - not to be missed	We stayed here on our return to SF after staying in a Travelodge for the beginning of our holiday. Booked on the recommendations of this site, and was not disappointed. The staff could not do more for us. We were given a late checkout, without being asked, until 14.30, so we could freshen up before our departure to SF International. We too sampled the wine and evening entertainment which was very relaxing after a hard day on the feet. The room was small compared with other rooms we stayed in in SF and Las Vegas, but standard compared with rooms in UK. Perfectly adequate for our stay and the safe, in the walk in closet, was a bonus. Rooms tastefully decorated and modern. Our bed was very comfortable. Area seemed run down but, as one reviewer has stated, there are homeless all over SF and, in fact, we didn't see any near the hotel although there looks to be a hostel nearby. Tip - buy a Muni pass. Excellent value which covers all the buses, BART and cable cars. We had our money's worth in the first day and, what could be more pleasant than catching the California cable car back to the hotel? Return stop only 2 blocks away and all downhill to the Carlton. The buses from Union Square go to the door and the buses to Union Square only one block away (downhill). We booked the limo service to the airport at the hotel desk. $45 compared with a taxi to the hotel of $40 (exc tips). So much nicer than the shuttle bus at £11 (with voucher per head) as it is direct and, as it turned out cheaper than the taxi, when we got stuck in traffic on the freeway! Ended the holiday in style. The BART $5.35 was not an option as we were carrying extra luggage for family.	
