Mar 26 2009 	Fabulous hotel great staff	Despite being on the edge of the Tenderloin (a 'dicey' area at times), I felt really safe traveling as a single female. It was in a great location for catching all modes of public transportation. Rooms were spotless, and the whole hotel has 'gone green' for the most part. I initially had a room that adjoined another, and found it to be really noisy - could hear the loud voices and TV of the people there. All I needed to do was request another room, and had one in moments, with the help of Marc at the front desk. Great local restaurants within walking distance, especially good finds for the 'budget-minded' traveler. The best feature of the hotel were the staff. Everyone, especially the evening staff - Marc, Theo and Edgar - were attentive, helpful, and really fun, as well as being highly professional and competent in their jobs. I would whole-heartedly recommend this hotel to anyone traveling to San Francisco. Just be warned about adjoining rooms - they can be noisy. Other rooms are quiet.	
