 luggage. When we went back to the hotel at 3 pm, they said the room was still not ready and asked us to wait for a while. We had to wait for nearly half an hour in the lobby before we could check in. After a 20-hour flight, we were tired and this long wait was annoying us more than usual. The funny thing was, we were not checked into the room that they said we were supposed to get. Apparently, during the period of our stay, the room we were supposed to be staying in needs to undergo certain renovation work. Luckily, the reception staff caught the problem in time and change our room before we went up - otherwise we would have to change our room during our stay. What I don't understand was why they had to make us wait in the lobby for so long instead of allocating another room to us since they have extra rooms? Then again, they checked us into a higher level room, which was probably why we didn't experience the same problem with noise as the other travellers did.	
