Feb 7 2009 	Excellent location but very noisy	We stayed here for 4 nights at the end of December 08. The room was small but comfortable, and we had a king-size bed. We got a really good rate on expedia.com. The Hotel Carlton is located a 10-minute walk from Union Square and we felt the area was safe (the hotel staff did tell us not to &quot;turn left&quot; in order to avoid the Tenderloin district). A lot of reviews on this site comment on the thin walls and I agree entirely. We heard every noise our neighbors made (including one person throwing up in the middle of the night).I give the hotel 5* for location but 1* for noise. I wouldn't stay there again because the noise bothered me. However, if you are a sound sleeper or don't mind being woken up, this is a great hotel.	
Feb 5 2009 	Excellent value and a great home base for exploring San Fran	I selected the Hotel Carlton for my husband and my 4-night stay in San Francisco because of its very reasonable rates, good location, and excellent TripAdvisor reviews. It is actually rated significantly better than many much more expensive hotels in the area. Well, as is most often the case, TripAdvisor came through for us yet again! We really enjoyed our stay at the Hotel Carlton, from the personal service to the ethnic decor to the convenient location; the fact that the hotel is &quot;green&quot; was another plus. The breakfast package, which includes a full breakfast at the in-house restaurant (Saha), is a great deal (definitely recommended). The waitress who served us each day was incredibly caring and sweet, and the food was plentiful and very tasty (good coffee also). We got a late start on our first morning and found that the restaurant was closing down early due to a lack of customers (most of the hotel guests ate early so as to get a jump start on sightseeing), but the waitress still managed to get together bowls of yogurt, granola, and fresh fruit for us (delicious and a perfect healthy start to the day), even though the kitchen was closed. The staff at the Hotel Carlton really go out of their way to treat their guests like family and ensure a great San Francisco experience. They tell you which areas of the city to avoid and can set you up with a variety of sightseeing packages if you don't already have your own plans. There is also a wine reception each night that encourages guests to mingle in the lovely lobby/living room area, which is complete with a charming fireplace. It was a little difficult to determine the timing of the wine service (seemed to differ a bit each day), and we had a pretty packed schedule, so we didn't get to actually partake during our stay, but it seemed like people were really enjoying themselves. The Hotel Carlton definitely attracts a more international crowd, with lots of Europeans. We really enjoyed the whole &quot;world&quot; vibe of the place. We were also very pleased with the room itself---the bed was very comfortable, and the ethnic decor was stylish. The bathroom was also nice and had eco-conscious features. Hotel rooms in San Francisco can be very small, but we found our room to be quite generous, especially given the large walk-in closet that provided tons of storage space for clothing and suitcases. It was possible to hear traffic/street noise from our room, but it wasn't so bad as to prevent us from sleeping (I always wear ear plugs anyway, which helps a lot). The location of the Hotel Carlton is great---unless you intend to take taxis everywhere, touring San Francisco requires a lot of walking and/or figuring out the myriad public transportation options, and the hotel's proximity to Union Square and the Powell-Mason cable car line is a big plus. The Nob Hill neighborhood is very nice, with plentiful coffee shops, cafés, bars, convenience stores, etc., and it's not too far a walk to Chinatown and beyond. We explored a wide variety of neighborhoods and attractions all throughout the city and found the Hotel Carlton to be a very good home base. If you're looking for economical accommodations in San Francisco but don't want to sacrifice comfort, quality, location, etc., then the Hotel Carlton is definitely the way to go. There is no doubt that we will be back, hopefully for a longer and more relaxed stay in the Bay Area.	
