May 12 2008 	Good hotel with great service!	My partner and I stayed here for 7 nights towards the end of April and enjoyed every minute of it. The hotel is very well located and accessible to all the more popular areas of San Francisco, such as Union square, Nob Hill and Pier 39 -- All within 5-10 minutes walk or tram ride away. The hotel itself is pretty good and for the price more than reasonable. The room we had was on the eight floor and although it wasn't in the best of condition it was still more than acceptable. It certainly wasn't shabby and we'd definitely stay here again. The hotel staff were more than friendly and are up there with some of the more expensive hotels we've stayed in over the years - Four Seasons for example. They were more than happy to help with anything you asked, from booking a taxi, recommending a restaurant, advice in things to do or see in the area and all with a smile. They certainly looked like they enjoyed their work and made you feel very welcome. The wine tasting every evening at 5:30 was also a nice touch, although we only made it back twice on our trip. San Francisco is just a great city and we could have spent a lot more time there. The only time we ate in the hotel was breakfast which was decent enough, again friendly service and good quality food. Would we recommend this hotel? Definitely, especially if you can get it for the price we paid which was about $95 a night.	
