Jan 21 2008 	Super Cute 	I took all the recommendations and comments from Tripadvisor in order to select the Hotel Carlton in SFO and it certainly lived up to all the opinions of my fellow travellers! Yes, the rooms aren't large, but they were very cosy. It was like visiting a friend's home, so of course there was no mini bar fridge in the room either. Noise is a factor, but that's because you are in the city so noise is inevitable! It didn't bother me at all, since i had expected it (from the reviews)!The heater noise was a bit frightful, but the hotel staff fixed it immediately and brought up a portable heater, which suited me fine since i'm not a big fan or aircon heaters anyway.The service was very personal and impeccable. The wine tasting from 5.30pm - 6pm is more like FREE wine in front of the fireplace!! I loved that extra bonus not to mention the free wireless internet! This hotel is the perfect place for holiday travellers who want a nice clean quaint place to stay in the heart of the SFO. I have no hesitations in going to the Hotel Carlton again!	
Jan 19 2008 	A nicely appointed room in a charming hotel	I had a great stay here for four nights surrounding the New Year 2008. My girlfriend and I stayed in a room on the 7th floor. It was small, but clean, pretty and relatively quiet. Do bring earplugs (as you should on any trip) since the soundproofing is not so great as to block out all hallway and street noise. Since we were there on New Year's Eve, there was a bit of street noise, but we went expecting it and it was fine.There were transvestite street walkers visible out the window and a number of meth-addicted bums on nearby streets, but they'll leave you alone for the most part. They have a nice restaurant called Saha on the ground floor. Try them out for great Arabic fusion food at a decent price.Parking was available at a lot across the street.Sorry, no photos of the hotel, but here are a few more of san fran.If you want to spend a little more money for a MUCH nicer experience, read my review on the Union St. Inn.	
Jan 14 2008 	Wonderful Experience!	I have nothing but good things to say about the Carlton. We did not really know what to expect when we booked rooms for my husband and myself, and one for our two college age sons, except that it had good reviews, was moderately priced (by San Francisco standards) and was well located in the city. From the moment we entered the attractive lobby and were greeted by the friendly, personable staff, we knew we'd made a good choice.The excellent, friendly service continued throughout our stay. The managers had helpful guides to city attractions, and made very good suggestions for local restaurants and cafes. There were many great breakfast places within easy walking distance, and a small grocery store and a Rite Aide, as well. Taxi service was swift and convenient. The Carlton also offers a wine bar happy hour each day.The rooms were attractively furnished and immaculate. The hotel also uses green practices, conserving water and energy which we appreciated. Last but not least, the Carlton has personality. So many chain hotels feel generic, but the Carlton instead feels unique and privately owned, although it is part of the Joie De Vivre chain. Based on our experience, I would seek out their hotels in other cities.Overall, we had an excellent experience and highly recommend the Carlton!	
Jan 4 2008 	Nice property friendly service but oh-so-thin walls ...	We booked for New Year's Eve, and picked the Carlton due to a combination of the positive ratings we found online, and the price, which was higher than we'd normally pay for a SF hotel, but hey ! - it was New Year's Eve, and there weren't any bargains to be had anywhere else (duh !). The hotel itself was an older building that had been nicely redone; the room was spacious enough, with nice furnishings and some neat large shutters on the floor to ceiling windows. The bathroom was clean and also in good shape, but had absolutely no counter space. As we got on the elevator to head up to our room, another guest raved to us about how friendly the staff had been to her (it was her 3rd day there) and how nice the free wine reception was, so we felt like we had made a good choice. One problem that became apparent quickly was after the sun went down, the room got cold, and there was no thermostat on the wall, just a grate-covered radiator in the room. We called down to the desk to ask how we could turn the heat on, and they said it was centrally controlled, and would be coming on in about 20 minutes. When it did come on, it made an impressive hissing sound and did warm up quickly, but for the rest of the night, the room temperature kept changing between too cold and too warm, which was frustrating and uncomfortable.The big problem came when our night of celebrating was over, and we got back to the room just before 2am. We had noticed when we arrived that the guests looked to be on the younger side (mid to late 20's), (we're early 50's), but didn't think twice about it - that is, until the room next door just started warming up their in-room celebration about the time we tried to hit the sack. (and ironicaly enough, we had to sign a &quot;no parties in the room&quot; form when we checked in). We were then &quot;treated&quot; , thanks to the Kleenex -thick walls, to being able to clearly hear virtually every conversation, scream, and whoop of the neighbors, who kept partying on, until about 3am, when I had finally had enough and banged as hard as I could on our wooden bed headboard, and they got the idea and toned it down a bit. But waking up with a hangover AND a lack of sleep didn't exactly get the New Year off to a great start.	
Jan 2 2008 	Best Staff Ever!	Johnny Lopez and Theo McKinney at the front desk were the best. The wine reception was a welcoming treat for the evening. All the people at the front desk could answer any question about the city and offered several options on local eateries, etc. They were just very laid back and easy to chat with. The lobby area was very cozy too. It felt like you were at a friends house with comfortable furniture. It had several seating types and areas and a very welcoming warm fireplace too for those cold rainy nights. The rooms were very cute and so clean. The bathrooms were large enough to do meet your needs, and decorated simply but nicely. A lot of hotels offer simple, but not clean or clean but hideously decorated. This had the best of both worlds. The location is very close to many restaurants, the cable car and China Town. We went to a great local coffee shop near the hotel called Quetzal (spelling?) which had great organic coffee and a warm environment that you get with the old coffee houses that unfortunately Starbucks doesn't offer. Overall, I would stay here again because the staff was so great, the rooms were very cute and the location was desirable.	
Jan 1 2008 	A great hotel - would stay here again!	We stayed at the Hotel Carlton in July 2007 for 7 nights. We were getting married at City Hall in SF and our mothers were staying at the hotel too so we got to see a variety of rooms. On check in we told them why we were in SF and they upgraded us to the top ‘Everest’ floor which has a water cooler and fresh apples in the corridor everyday. Our room wasn’t huge, but we had no need for it to be bigger. As the other reviews state, you can hear your neighbours at times but this only really bothered us on one occasion. Street noise was unnoticeable except for the occasional emergency vehicle siren. Being on the upper floors the views were un-obscured and the windows both had screens, between buildings we could just see the bay. The room was light and airy.Our mothers were on one of the lower floors and their windows looked out at other buildings which wasn’t exactly pretty and made the room darker. But at the end of the day, it’s not as though our purpose in SF was to spend time in the room looking out of the windows! The sink in my mum’s room got blocked and on notifying the front desk they moved her and upgraded her room to the top floor to make up for the inconvenience.The reception desk staff were always very helpful, as mentioned in other reviews, especially Theo who always gave great service with a big smile. On our wedding day he arranged for a limo to take us to City Hall (paid for by the hotel) and on our return had placed a cake in a heart made of rose petals and a bottle of wine on the bed. It was so thoughtful and wonderful surprise to finish the day.We ate breakfast at the hotel restaurant, although found some things to be a little over-spiced for so early in the day. We also had dinner here and everyone in our party enjoyed their meals.The hotel isn’t perfectly placed for all of the sights, but it really isn’t that difficult to get about using the public transport. I would definitely stay here again and would recommend the hotel to others. My dad stayed at a hotel 2 blocks up the road which was roughly the same price and said that by comparison the Carlton was a much better choice.We later went on to Las Vegas and stayed in the pyramid at the Luxor. Whilst the room there was bigger than at the Carlton, we found the cleanliness, décor, comfort and particularly the staff at the Luxor, didn’t even compare to the Carlton.	
