Oct 28 2007	fantastic hotel at a great price	I stayed at the Hotel Carlton for four nights in mid October, as a solo female traveler I was a bit nervous about being ever so slightly out of the hub of the city but had a fantastic stay at the Hotel Carlton. Location - you can walk to Union Square in 15 minutes, perfectly safe but would recommend a cab at night if on your own. Buy a three day muni pass for $18 and catch the cable car (1 block away) and nearby buses to get easily and cheaply about. I always felt safe and there were lots of handy shops and eating/snack places nearby.Rooms - gorgeous good sized, spotlessly clean, modern and comfortable rooms with large bathrooms and a huge closet. I was upgraded to a top floor room with great views of the city. There is also free fruit, filtered water, tea and coffee. The bed was huge and comfy with lots of pillows and extra blankets if you needed them, a hairdryer, CD player and iron, plenty of towels and generous bathrobes. Lobby - a real fire, plenty of comfortable chairs and sofas, newspapers, books etc and best of all free wine every evening. A friendly, cozy and welcoming place to hang out.Staff - the hotel staff were brilliant. Nothing was too much trouble, any question you had, travel plans you needed help with, without exception you were helped with a smile and good information. Every time I entered the hotel I was warmly welcomed, my luggage was stored when I arrived early and left late, they booked my airport shuffle and I was asked a number of times if everything was to my liking. The staff obviously got on well and were happy in their job and it showed, they were the nicest I've experienced in any hotel - not one grump!Price - in a city where rooms seem to average $300 a night, I paid less than half this booking direct with the hotel and the value for money was excellent.There was only one downside to staying at this hotel and I don't know what they can do about it - the walls are thin and if you have inconsiderate neighbours like I did on the last night it can be very annoyong - watching Bruce Willis movies at 6am full volume! Take your ear plugs and book at the Hotel Carlton for great prices and a smashing little hotel.	
