Oct 24 2007 	Good hotel but bring your earplugs	We stayed at the Hotel Carlton for four nights in October 2007. After having read the reviews on this website I e-mailed the hotel in advance and asked them to allocate us a quiet room. Unfortunately I cannot remember the number of the room we were eventually allocated, but whilst we did not hear noise from other bedrooms, the noise from the street below during the nights was very loud. I do remember that we stayed on the eighth floor and our room overlooked the street to the side of the hotel rather than Sutter Street. I would recommend bringing ear plugs if you are going to stay at this hotel.Despite this, we enjoyed our stay at the Hotel Carlton. The room was spacious enough for us. There was a large wardrobe with ironing board and iron. There was a hairdryer provided and a radio alarm clock with CD player. The room was extermely clean and well serviced each day. The hotel is a 15 minute walk to Union Square, but is on a main bus route to a number of places. We purchased a travel card and got around a lot of places, including Haight Ashbury, Pacific Heights, Golden Gate Bridge by bus. The reception staff were very helpful when we asked them queries. The wine reception is a lovely touch which we appreciated after a hard day walking the streets of San Francisco.I would have no hesitation in recommending the hotel to people, as long as they take earplugs along with them for the street noise!	
Oct 19 2007	Some high and some low points - overall would not return	We stayed at this hotel for 2 nights earlier this month. We selected the property based on positive reviews on this website and on balance, we were underwhelmed by our experience here. Here's what we experienced:High Points:- Friendly, warm welcome/check-in- clean, functional room with funky, modern decor- high quality linens, toiletries, towels etc- wine reception in lobby from 5:30-6pm Low Points:- 2nd floor room overlooking laneway beside hotel was exceptionally noisy and, laneway seemed to be a &quot;smoking area&quot; - cigarette smoke wafting up made it impossible to leave windows open and was so bad, we had to put the ceiling fan on high and open our door to let the room &quot;air out&quot;- Noise from lobby. Loud music is played in the lobby overnight and, into the early morning hours. Music carrys up the stairs to second floor and was clearly audible in the room. - walls are very thin and conversations from hall/neighbouring rooms were clearly audibleThe front desk attendant to whom we mentioned these concerns was unapologetic and simply acknowledged our feedback. I didn't ask to switch rooms given we only had one night left in our stay however, the overall experience would deter us from staying here again and, recommending this hotel to others.	
