Oct 6 2007 	Very nice Hotel	My wife and I chose this Hotel on the basis of reviews on here, and to be honest, most views were pretty accurate. We stayed from the 12th to the 19th of September, and booked as part of a 3 week tour of San Francisco, Vegas and Orlando through United Vacations (flight experiences are another story).On arrival we were greeted at reception by a cheery welcome, given guide maps and informed of the wine tasting in the evening (complimentary every night).The Hotel is an older property, but is maintained in very good order. Our bedroom was on the 7th floor, and we got the corner room, looking up Sutter Street. Traffic noise was in evidence, and the creche next door was audible, but was not a problem noise wise. However I agree that there is little sound deadening between rooms, but no worse than other Hotels we have stayed in. The room was always kept in great order by housekeeping, and in fact any staff we spoke to went out of their way to make us feel welcome (an alien concept in some Hotels).We didn't use the Hotel restaurant due it not being to our taste, but it seemed popular at all times.There were however plenty places to eat locally, and we never once felt intimidated walking around the area - we had been advised not to go to the Tenderloin area, so kept to It's fringes (you will find the homeless in any city nowadays) and were never accosted.With regard to situation within the City, the hotel is about 5 blocks from Union Square - an easy (for us) 10 minute walk. We also walked down to the Embarcadero, then along the front to Fisherman's Wharf one day, then walked directly to the Wharf another - not too far (again for us).We did however purchase the multi day pass for transport, and this was great as it covered all modes of travel ( we used this to get to Golden Gate park - but the museums are closed on Mondays).We experienced a spell of particularly good weather for our stay, and neither of us ever had more than short sleeve shirts on due to the warmth.To conclude, I would recommend this Hotel to anyone - it may not be the lap of luxury, but it is well run, clean and good value for money.Pete and Linda Sinclair Broughty Ferry Scotland	
