Sep 3 2007 	Outstanding!	I checked out the reviews here before booking, and I was not disappointed. This place is NOT the ultimate in posh, but it is nice, clean, safe and an EXCELLENT value. Lots of Europeans stay here and it has that sort of 'travelling in Europe' vibe to it. Yes, the folks at the front desk really will go out of their way to help you and see that you have an enjoyable stay. Yes, there is a free wine reception in the lobby every day from 5:30-6:00 pm. They literally close it at 6 pm, so if you miss it, there's always tomorrow. I was hoping to meet other travellers and potential dinner companions at the wine reception, but it really does not happen. People just drink with their friends/relatives and very little socializing happens between people who don't already know each other. As other travellers say, this place is about a 10-block walk from things you might want to see downtown. I suggest familiarizing yourself with the bus routes, or bringing some really good walking shoes, or simply be prepared to unload lots of cash on cabs. The BART (metro) is not terribly far, however, BART does not go to all the places you might want to go in the city. Skip eating the overpriced breakfast at the hotel's 'Arab-fusion' restaurant - there are several cute places within 2 or 3 blocks serving breakfast. Internet access is $10/hour to use the hotel's terminals, or there is wifi but I think they charge for that too. I thoroughly enjoyed this hotel and would definitely go back.	
