Aug 5 2007 	Three Night Stay at the Hotel Carlton	My boyfriend and I stayed three nights at the Hotel Carlton in San Francisco and found the hotel to be average. We read a number of reviews of the hotel on trip advisor and decided to give it a try. As other reviewers have commented, this hotel is very &quot;basic&quot;. My boyfriend described the decor as &quot;furniture from Goodwill&quot; and we had a view of an graffiti scribbled parking lot. However, the room was clean and the staff was friendly. In addition, the entire hotel is non-smoking and there is a cute lobby/living room area with a fireplace. Other reviewers complained about noise from adjacent rooms and I agree. We could most definitely hear our neighbors talking and one morning were awakened by loud banging coming from the room next door. In addition, we would frequently hear staff talking loudly in the hall. Overall, the hotel is adequate (2 stars) - not a &quot;nice&quot; hotel. We paid $120 per night which, for this time of year, is about the best centrally located hotel we could get for this rate.	
Aug 5 2007	Great Value 	We stayed here for one night and will definitely be back! Lobby was light and modern with lots of comfortable seating - and a nightly wine reception from 5:30-6:00. A lot of fun to gather with the other guests over free wine before heading out for the evening - and a most unexpected perk from such a well-priced hotel. Room was clean and comfortable, enjoyed the modern yet historic 1920's feel of the place. We purchased the overnight &quot;parking package&quot; and the hotel gladly held our car &amp; baggage after checkout the next day so we could go enjoy the city for the day. Service was friendly and accommodating (recommended a great little restaurant near our theater). We enjoyed the location being in a clean neighborhood within walking distance (1/2 mile?) from Union Square and the theater we were headed to - but away from all the madness and bustle of the tourists. No complaints about location - felt it was safe and quiet. Will definitely stay here again, can't think of any negatives at all!	
Aug 4 2007 	Perfect choice for SF	My girlfriend and I recently stayed at the carlton for 5 nights after a 4 week drive across the US and couldn't have picked anywhere better. The hotel is modern and clean, our room was large with a comfortable bed, excellent bathroom and a very large walk in closet (with safe). The staff couldn't have been more friendly and helpful. And, contrary to other reviews, we found nothing wrong with the neighborhood. We used a nearby store, laundrette, hairdresser and breakfast dinner. And we walked home several nights the couple of blocks from union square without any hassle. Would definitely recommend to any european travelling to San Francisco looking for a good hotel at a reasonable rate.	
Aug 4 2007	Thank you Theo	I have worked in a lot of hotels as a receptionist and I have to say the team at the Carlton could put anybody to shame. My partner and I were feeling stressed out when we checked in (driving in SF is a nightmare, particularly for UK drivers who don't know where they're going) and Theo (the receptionist) put a smile back on both our faces, he was just very very good at his job and so friendly! He happened to notice that i was going to be turning 30 the next day (ID required to check in) and wished me a happy birthday, which I thought was very nice and I certainly didn't expect more.. but when we returned to our room that evening it had been decorated with balloons and there was a bottle of wine, two glasses, and a piece of chocolate cake sitting on the table, talk about amazing customer service and going the extra mile! Things you hear about all the time in the hotel business but are never really put into practice, not to that extent anyway! The hotel itself was nice and clean, look like it had recently been refurbished and everything in the room worked: shower, tv, hair dryer (proper one) safe etc. It is also within walking distance of a lot of bars, restaurants and Union Square. We loved it and would definitely stay there again as it is a great hotel, Theo just made it extra special for us. So I would like to say thank you.	
Jul 29 2007 	Interesting Hotel Bad Location	My wife and I stayed for one night at the Hotel Carlton in June. Like many older hotels in San Francisco, the Carlton offers an interesting view into the city's architectural history (built in 1927) with contemporary and stylish interior design. The front desk staff was courteous and helpful, and in the late afternoon glasses of wine were offered in the lobby to hotel guests. The best part of the stay was the amazing restaurant Saha on the first floor of the hotel. Saha specializes in Arabic-fusion cuisine, and everything we ate and drank was outstanding. That said, there were a few problems with the hotel. The bathroom door would not close completely (the latch was too short) and there was no screen on our eighth-floor window, which left my mildly acrophobic wife a bit terrified when she stuck her head out the open window to see an eight-story drop into an alley below (those with children beware). Those are minor concerns, however, and didn't bother us much. More significant concerns were the extremely thin walls and the hotel's proximity to a hospital with an emergency room, which meant we heard extremely loud sirens throughout the night. The hotel also borders San Francisco's Tenderloin neighborhood, which is not exactly the most family-friendly. There are numerous XXX adult establishments near the hotel, and although we had great sympathy for the scores of homeless indidivuals we passed by, my wife was a little concerned for her safety on a few occasions.Overall, we thoroughly enjoyed the Carlton itself, but its poor location (noise and bad neighborhood) might prompt us to look for an alternative the next time we're in the city.	
